// Onboarding API Routes
// REST API endpoint router for the onboarding feature. Handles config, categories,
// graph, topics, diagrams, search, users, progress, notes, and team endpoints.
// Delegates topic reads to KodexManager; all other data comes from OnboardingManager
// or OnboardingDbService. The database connection is closed in a finally block
// after each request.

FUNCTION handleOnboardingAPI(req) -> Response                              EXPORT
  CALLS: OnboardingManager (onboarding-manager), OnboardingDbService (onboarding-db), getKodexManager (kodex-manager)
  Require the "project" query parameter; return 400 if missing.
  Instantiate OnboardingManager and OnboardingDbService for the project.
  Route the request by path suffix and HTTP method:

  OnboardingManager routes:
    GET /config      -> return manager.getConfig()
    GET /categories  -> return manager.getCategories()
    GET /graph       -> return manager.getGraph()

  Topic routes (delegated to KodexManager):
    GET /topics          -> return kodex.listTopics()
    GET /topics/:name    -> return kodex.getTopic(name, full content); 404 if missing
    GET /topics/:name/diagram -> return manager.getDiagram(name)

  Search:
    GET /search?q=...&scope=... -> call dbService.search(q, scope); return results
    Return 400 if q is missing.

  Users:
    GET  /users          -> dbService.listUsers()
    POST /users          -> dbService.createUser(name); return 201
      Return 400 if name is blank. Return 409 on UNIQUE constraint violation.
    GET  /users/:id      -> dbService.getUser(id); return 404 if not found

  Progress:
    GET    /progress/:userId           -> dbService.getUserProgress(userId)
    POST   /progress/:userId/:topic    -> dbService.markProgress(userId, topic, status)
      Accepts status "explored" or "skipped"; return 400 for invalid values.
    DELETE /progress/:userId/:topic    -> dbService.deleteProgress(userId, topic); return 204

  Notes:
    GET    /notes/:userId/:topic       -> dbService.getNotes(userId, topic)
    POST   /notes/:userId/:topic       -> dbService.addNote(userId, topic, content); return 201
      Return 400 if content is blank.
    PUT    /notes/:noteId              -> dbService.editNote(noteId, content)
      Return 400 if content is blank.
    DELETE /notes/:noteId              -> dbService.deleteNote(noteId); return 204

  Team:
    GET /team -> dbService.getTeam()

  Return 404 for unmatched routes.
  Return 500 with the error message on unexpected exceptions.
  Always close the dbService connection in the finally block.

---

FUNCTION jsonError(message, status) -> Response
  Wrap a message string in { error } and return it with the given HTTP status.
